text: Damn...I just watched this movie today and all I can say is wow! This is definitely a standout movie from a year that would be meh if it weren't for a few good movies. It is intense and entertaining, with some good acting and some funny quips here and there, along with some good drama that makes it intense and keeps your eyes glued to the screen. Not to mention the soundtrack is awesome! Not that much action as the trailer might lead you to believe, but the drama and acting makes it intense. The tone of the movie is great as well, with some really nice comedy and drama, and not too serious until the final act. However, it still managed to keep me on the edge of my seat. Also, I love good cinematography and this is no exception. Runtime is good too. Really, REALLY impressed on this one. However, I didn't like how the writing sometimes wasn't good but in other places it was strong. That does, however, knock it down some points and it is not perfect so I would give it an 8.5/10. Really good tho

It's like a mash up of Blow, Lord of War and Wolf of Wall Street. I think it needed a better trailer because it presents itself as a comedy or farce of the genre. This was probably made to look like a certain type of film to get a certain demographic but it's tone is more of a real film instead of some dumb comedy of the month. It's actually just as serious a film as the ones I mentioned however it does have some good humor throughout that works well with the story and of course it's not a dead pan drama because of this, it tries to be a fun film and takes itself lightly in a way that works to reflect the weird time the Bush era was in these days. If you like any of the 3 films I mentioned you'd enjoy it, it's a very cool movie.

text: Went into this movie with caution and scepticism expecting another obnoxious, bloated movie and was pleasantly surprised when i discovered it is stylish, charming, colorful, dynamic and constantly entertaining film. What worked here and what this movie relied on is main two guys who give really energetic and dashing performances, you buy that they are old buddies, their chemistry and the way they rubbed each other worked so much. Story itself was also intriguing and riveting sometimes uneven, but never to the point of losing interest or becoming tiresome or idiotic. It has its own identity in a way because it shows in highly satirical way how USA is open door for anyone to make money, no matter who or what their backgrounds are. It is capitalism at its core and it worked in this film. In the end it is not anything new, it follows that same gangsta formula playing out exactly how you think, but nevertheless it is charismatic two hour entertainment and i say go check it out.
